Oman Air to Name New Chief Executive Officer, The National Says

-- B y   T a m a r a   W a l i d
-- 
2011-08-21T04:57:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/oman-air-to-name-new-chief-executive-officer-the-national-says.html
Oman Air, the sultanate’s state-
owned carrier, will soon announce a replacement for Chief
Executive Officer Peter Hill, who plans to retire next month,
 The National  newspaper said, citing the company.  British airline BMI’s CEO Wolfgang Prock-Schauer is a
candidate for the role, the paper reported, without saying where
it got the information. BMI is a unit of Deutsche Lufthansa AG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tamara Walid in Abu Dhabi at 
 twalid@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  